**Edit: This comment is invalid in favor of reason mentioned here #2635**

I think default env config was intentionally removed since i am not exactly aware why but there is warning in comments. Could we explicitly set just `TERM=xterm` more like

```diff
--- a/run_linux.go
+++ b/run_linux.go
@@ -101,7 +101,7 @@ func (b *Builder) Run(command []string, options RunOptions) error {
        }

        // hardwire the environment to match docker build to avoid subtle and hard-to-debug differences due to containers.conf
-       b.configureEnvironment(g, options, []string{"PATH=/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin"})
+       b.configureEnvironment(g, options, []string{"PATH=/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin", "TERM=xterm"})

        if b.CommonBuildOpts == nil {
                return errors.Errorf("Invalid format on container you must recreate the container")
```
